result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Christopher Deleon was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Christopher Deleon in court with attorney Andrew Charles Ladd.  Lucas Paul Bennewitz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 2 dismissed by operation of law.  Case 14TR7643 dismissed and read in to this matter.

Court orders the following: 
- Total sentence: 5 years (Initial Confinement: 2 years, Extended Supervision: 3 years) STAYED.  Credit for 3 days if revoked.
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration
- Defendant IS eligible for Substance Abuse Program
- 3 years Probation
- 36 months Drivers License Revocation. 
- 36 months Ignition Interlock on any vehicle TITLED OR REGISTERED to defendant 
- Alcohol Assessment
- Cash bail to be refunded to poster
- Fine of $1,393.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- Blood Test Reimbursement of $35.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forwarded to Waukesha County Sheriff's Department
- DNA Surcharge of $250.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
- Conditions of Probation:  Maintain absolute sobriety/Random UAs.  No use or possession of alcohol/drug paraphernalia/drugs without a valid prescription.  Defendant is not to go into any establishment whose primary purpose is to sell alcoholic beverages.  Attend a minimum of 2 self help meetings per week.  Maintain full-time employment and/or school.
CONDITION TIME: 9 months - NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - To commence FORTHWITH.  Condition time may be served in Jefferson County.
Defendant was remanded to the custody of the Sheriff to commence the sentence.
